    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Process in which images are transferred by painting a wet acrylic medium on a paper print and subsequently rubbing the paper away, leaving only the colorant, toner, or ink embedded in the acrylic. </Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000052951/Hill, Use of Acrylic Transfers as Alternative Collage-Making Method, Leonardo (1980)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000052953/Howell-Koehler, Photo Art Processes (1980)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Procedé waarbij afbeeldingen worden overgebracht door het schilderen van nat acryl op een papieren afdruk, waarna het papier wordt weggewreven waardoor alleen de kleurstof, toner of inkt in het acryl resteert. </Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>一種轉印技法，藉由將壓克力溶劑塗在一張紙板畫上，後直接摩擦紙板以壓印圖案並將紙張至壓克力上移除，最終只留下紙上的著色劑、調色劑或者是油墨附著在壓克力版上形成圖案。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000250/AS-Academia Sinica</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
